, and develop a nuanced sense of selfhood that draws on endurance, asceticism, mobility, and citizenship.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPoor womenxHealth and hygienezIndiazDelhi. 0aPoor womenzIndiazDelhixSocial conditions. 0aWell-beingzIndiazDelhi. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aasceticism.  acitizenship.  adelhi slum.  adelhi.  ademolition.  aendurance.  afamily.  agender and women studies.  agender studies.  ahealth.  ahuman condition.  aimpoverished women.  aindependence.  aindia.  ainequality.  amobility.  amoral citizenship.  amoral strategies.  amorality.  aneighbors.  apoor.  apoverty.  apublic policy.  arelationships.  aselfhood.  asetting boundaries.  aslum environment.  asocial services.  asurvival.  aurban cities.  aurban slums.  aurban studies.  aurban.  awell being.  awomen living in slums.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052028480740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096050340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520960503423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520960503/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY